Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract This paper examines how shocks to government bond duration risk held by price-sensitive investors affect the euro area term structure of interest rates and the wider macroeconomy. We construct a new measure of the bond ?free float,? which adjusts total debt for foreign official holdings and weights by residual maturity. Using a small macrofinance Bayesian Vector Autoregression (VAR) model, we estimate that the first round of asset purchases under the European Central Bank's (ECB) public sector purchase program reduced euro area 10-year bond yields by around 30 bps in 2015. The positive impact on the output gap and inflation in 2016 was about 0.2 and 0.3 ppt, respectively.
ER  - 

